description.narrative: Output 1.5 Nutrition systems in Yemen are better able to support delivery of multi-sectorial nutrition interventions, including both preventive and curative care at facility and community levels., which contributes to Child Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more vulnerable neonates, infants and children survive and thrive and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth
